# userrepair is a fully offline desktop application and requires NO environment
# variables at runtime. This file exists only to document that fact.
#
# The two optional variables below affect the dev server / build only:

# Host to bind the Vite dev server to when developing against a device on the LAN
# (used by `npm run tauri:dev`). Leave unset for normal local development.
# TAURI_DEV_HOST=

# No API keys, secrets, database URLs, or service endpoints are used anywhere.
# All data is stored locally in SQLite under the OS app-data directory.
